    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck is a bit risky, but fun.  Works great vs setting up shadows like Sauron wounding.  Bids 3 to ensure going first.  Pulls Ever my heart rises, and uses suspended palaces and come here lad to stack on it like crazy.  With Axe of Erebor can make sure Gimli wins his fights easy.  Double to site 3.  You will have a smeagol card to run to 6, then either run home or walk if easier.<br />
<br />
Shadow mainly based on getting Grima Wormtongue to clog up their hands to make it easier for fellowship to run.  <br />
<br />
You can&#39;t afford to walk with this deck, as you will run out of cards fast.  Always atleast double unless its definite suicide. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
